sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1725302
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Member of the RBS library - derived from BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Parts K1725225-K1725256 are members of ribosome binding site library derived from Anderson-family RBS B0032 (BBa_B0032). All 32 sequences were obtained by randomised PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vilija Lomeikaite
